cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it deals with Constraint Programming (CP), which is a powerful declarative programming paradigm combining inference and search in order to find solutions to various types of constraint systems. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for implementing stratified constructive disjunction and negation on top of an existing CP solver, which is a topic of interest in the AI community. 

The paper is also likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category as it proposes a new library for implementing stratified and constructive reasoning for various operators, including disjunction and negation, implication and conditional. 

The Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category is also a likely fit as the paper deals with reasoning and inference in constraint systems, which is a topic of interest in the logic community. 

The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category is a possible fit as the paper proposes a new approach for handling highly disjunctive constraint systems, which involves search and inference algorithms. 

Finally, the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category is a possible fit as the paper proposes a new library for implementing stratified and constructive reasoning, which is a software engineering task.
